aiSLCAnalog.name: aiSLCAnalog
aiSLCAnalog.contactinfo: Engineering MIB Administrator Postal: Applied Innovation Inc. 5800 Innovation Drive Dublin, Ohio 43017-3271 Tel: 614-798-2000 Fax: 614-798-1770 Email: snmp@aiinet.com
aiSLCAnalog.description: MIB module for SLCs with analog input points.

aiSLCAnalogInputTable.name: aiSLCAnalogInputTable
aiSLCAnalogInputTable.description: Table of analog inputs points indexed by point number. Includes description, configuration and status information.

aislcainPointNumber.name: aislcainPointNumber
aislcainPointNumber.description: Input point number to which this table row applies.

aislcainScanningEnabled.name: aislcainScanningEnabled
aislcainScanningEnabled.description: Enable or disable scanning of the input.

aislcainDescription.name: aislcainDescription
aislcainDescription.description: Textual description of the point. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcainNormalStateTrap.name: aislcainNormalStateTrap
aislcainNormalStateTrap.description: If enabled, transitions from an alarm state to the normal state will generate an SNMP trap or TL1 message.

aislcainHighAlarmSeverity.name: aislcainHighAlarmSeverity
aislcainHighAlarmSeverity.description: Severity of the point's alarm state, or notReported(5) if the point does not generate an alarm.

aislcainHighAlarmStateText.name: aislcainHighAlarmStateText
aislcainHighAlarmStateText.description: Textual description of the point's alarm state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcainLowAlarmSeverity.name: aislcainLowAlarmSeverity
aislcainLowAlarmSeverity.description: Severity of the point's alarm state, or notReported(5) if the point does not generate an alarm.

aislcainLowAlarmStateText.name: aislcainLowAlarmStateText
aislcainLowAlarmStateText.description: Textual description of the point's alarm state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcainNormalStateText.name: aislcainNormalStateText
aislcainNormalStateText.description: Textual description of the point's normal state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcainUserUnits.name: aislcainUserUnits
aislcainUserUnits.description: The user-defined units for this input (e.g. degC, degF, etc.).

aislcainMinInputmA.name: aislcainMinInputmA
aislcainMinInputmA.description: The current in mA corresponding to the minimum input in user-defined units.

aislcainMinInputuu.name: aislcainMinInputuu
aislcainMinInputuu.description: The minimum value in user-defined units corresponding to the minimum input in mA.

aislcainMaxInputmA.name: aislcainMaxInputmA
aislcainMaxInputmA.description: The current in mA corresponding to the maximum input in user-defined units.

aislcainMaxInputuu.name: aislcainMaxInputuu
aislcainMaxInputuu.description: The maximum value in user-defined units corresponding to the maximum input in mA.

aislcainHighLimitScan.name: aislcainHighLimitScan
aislcainHighLimitScan.description: If enabled, the high limit threshold will be checked when the input is scanned.

aislcainHighAlarmThresholduu.name: aislcainHighAlarmThresholduu
aislcainHighAlarmThresholduu.description: The high alarm level in user-defined units.

aislcainHighAlarmThresholdIntervaluu.name: aislcainHighAlarmThresholdIntervaluu
aislcainHighAlarmThresholdIntervaluu.description: The high alarm level threshold interval in user-defined units. When the high alarm is active, each time the input rises another interval higher, a new alarm is sent.

aislcainHighAlarmMinPeriod.name: aislcainHighAlarmMinPeriod
aislcainHighAlarmMinPeriod.description: The minimum number of seconds the input(s) should be energized when the input exceeds the high alarm threshold.

aislcainHighAlarmHysteresisuu.name: aislcainHighAlarmHysteresisuu
aislcainHighAlarmHysteresisuu.description: The amount by which the input must drop below the High Alarm Threshold before the High Alarm will be cleared.

aislcainLowLimitScan.name: aislcainLowLimitScan
aislcainLowLimitScan.description: If enabled, the low limit threshold will be checked when the input is scanned.

aislcainLowAlarmThresholduu.name: aislcainLowAlarmThresholduu
aislcainLowAlarmThresholduu.description: The low alarm level in user-defined units.

aislcainLowAlarmThresholdIntervaluu.name: aislcainLowAlarmThresholdIntervaluu
aislcainLowAlarmThresholdIntervaluu.description: The low alarm level threshold interval in user-defined units. When the low alarm is active, each time the input drops another interval lower, a new alarm is sent.

aislcainLowAlarmMinPeriod.name: aislcainLowAlarmMinPeriod
aislcainLowAlarmMinPeriod.description: The minimum number of seconds the input(s) should be energized when the input falls below the low alarm threshold.

aislcainLowAlarmHysteresisuu.name: aislcainLowAlarmHysteresisuu
aislcainLowAlarmHysteresisuu.description: The amount by which the input must rise above the Low Alarm Threshold before the Low Alarm will be cleared.

aislcainCurrentValueuu.name: aislcainCurrentValueuu
aislcainCurrentValueuu.description: The current input value in user-defined units.

aislcainCurrentValuemA.name: aislcainCurrentValuemA
aislcainCurrentValuemA.description: The current input value in mA.

aislcainLastChangeTime.name: aislcainLastChangeTime
aislcainLastChangeTime.description: Textural representation of the time of the most recent output change. 24-hour format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.

aislcaintl1AccessID.name: aislcaintl1AccessID
aislcaintl1AccessID.description: Unique TL1 access identifier for this point. Maximum length is 22 characters.

aislcaintl1Provisioned.name: aislcaintl1Provisioned
aislcaintl1Provisioned.description: Enable TL1 management of this point.

aislcaintl1AccessIDType.name: aislcaintl1AccessIDType
aislcaintl1AccessIDType.description: Identifies the point as either an equipment(1) alarm condition or an environmental(2) alarm.

aislcaintl1HighAlarmType.name: aislcaintl1HighAlarmType
aislcaintl1HighAlarmType.description: String indicating the type of alarm, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is environmental(2). Maximum length is 10 characters.

aislcaintl1HighAlarmMessage.name: aislcaintl1HighAlarmMessage
aislcaintl1HighAlarmMessage.description: Textual description of the alarm, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is environmental(2). Maximum length is 40 characters.

aislcaintl1LowAlarmType.name: aislcaintl1LowAlarmType
aislcaintl1LowAlarmType.description: String indicating the type of alarm, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is environmental(2). Maximum length is 10 characters.

aislcaintl1LowAlarmMessage.name: aislcaintl1LowAlarmMessage
aislcaintl1LowAlarmMessage.description: Textual description of the alarm, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is environmental(2). Maximum length is 40 characters.

aislcaintl1HighAlarmNotificationCode.name: aislcaintl1HighAlarmNotificationCode
aislcaintl1HighAlarmNotificationCode.description: Severity of the point's alarm state.

aislcaintl1HighAlarmServiceAffecting.name: aislcaintl1HighAlarmServiceAffecting
aislcaintl1HighAlarmServiceAffecting.description: Indicates whether or not the alarm affects the functioning of the equipment. This is only meaningful when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1).

aislcaintl1HighAlarmConditionType.name: aislcaintl1HighAlarmConditionType
aislcaintl1HighAlarmConditionType.description: String indicating the type of alarm condition, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1). Maximum length is 20 characters.

aislcaintl1HighAlarmConditionDesc.name: aislcaintl1HighAlarmConditionDesc
aislcaintl1HighAlarmConditionDesc.description: Textual description of the alarm condition, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1). Maximum length is 64 characters.

aislcaintl1LowAlarmNotificationCode.name: aislcaintl1LowAlarmNotificationCode
aislcaintl1LowAlarmNotificationCode.description: Severity of the point's alarm state.

aislcaintl1LowAlarmServiceAffecting.name: aislcaintl1LowAlarmServiceAffecting
aislcaintl1LowAlarmServiceAffecting.description: Indicates whether or not the alarm affects the functioning of the equipment. This is only meaningful when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1).

aislcaintl1LowAlarmConditionType.name: aislcaintl1LowAlarmConditionType
aislcaintl1LowAlarmConditionType.description: String indicating the type of alarm condition, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1). Maximum length is 20 characters.

aislcaintl1LowAlarmConditionDesc.name: aislcaintl1LowAlarmConditionDesc
aislcaintl1LowAlarmConditionDesc.description: Textual description of the alarm condition, used only when aislcaintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1). Maximum length is 64 characters.

aislcainAnalogStatus.name: aislcainAnalogStatus
aislcainAnalogStatus.description: The current alarm status of the analog input.

aislcainCurrentStateText.name: aislcainCurrentStateText
aislcainCurrentStateText.description: Textual description of the point's current state. This is either aislcainNormalStateText or aislcainAlarmStateText.

aislcainAnalogAlarmState.name: aislcainAnalogAlarmState
aislcainAnalogAlarmState.description: The point's current alarm state, or normal(5).
